The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Geyserville had a population of 861. The population density was {{convert|190.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Geyserville was 471 (54.7%) [[White Americans|White]], 4 (0.5%) [[African Americans|African American]], 26 (3.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 18 (2.1%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 2 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 191 (22.2%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 149 (17.3%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 342 persons (39.7%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Geyserville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0629420 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 302 households, out of which 68 (22.5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 156 (51.7%) were married-couple households, 15 (5.0%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 63 (20.9%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 68 (22.5%) had a male householder with no partner present. 81 households (26.8%) were one person, and 48 (15.9%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.85.<ref name=DP1/> There were 195 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (64.6% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Geyserville CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0629420 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 164 people (19.0%) under the age of 18, 55 people (6.4%) aged 18 to 24, 197 people (22.9%) aged 25 to 44, 248 people (28.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 197 people (22.9%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 45.9{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 109.5 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 339 housing units at an average density of {{convert|75.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 302 (89.1%) were occupied. Of these, 219 (72.5%) were owner-occupied, and 83 (27.5%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

